This paper deals with the extraction and analysis of graphs from relational databases, which falls under the domain of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a domain-specific language for graph extraction and introduces novel algorithms for graph compression, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the trade-offs between memory usage and computational cost, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
